<subSubSection id="C89655E1E349805CFF70FD054574FCC8" pageId="2" pageNumber="1645" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8033066AE349805CFF70FD054574FCC8" blockId="2.[178,1085,741,880]" pageId="2" pageNumber="1645">
Comment: This wing-dimorphic species was previously known from the Chinese provinces Gansu, Shaanxi, Hubei, Sichuan, and Jiangsu (
<bibRefCitation id="E41D7B9BE349805CFD36FCE247ADFCA0" author="ASSING V" box="[756,905,770,792]" pageId="2" pageNumber="1645" pagination="53 - 128" refId="ref6350" refString="ASSING V. (2013 c): On the Lathrobium fauna of China V. New species and additional records from Yunnan (Coleoptera: Staphylinidae: Paederinae). - Contributions to Entomology, Beitrage zur Entomologie 63 (1) (2013): 53 - 128." type="journal article" year="2013">ASSING 2013c</bibRefCitation>
). Recently, it was reported also from 
<collectingCountry id="F89B46FAE349805CFEBFFCC04593FC8D" box="[381,439,800,821]" name="Japan" pageId="2" pageNumber="1645">Japan</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation id="E41D7B9BE349805CFE05FCC04644FC8E" author="ASSING V" box="[455,608,800,822]" pageId="2" pageNumber="1645" pagination="1615 - 1641" refId="ref6442" refString="ASSING V. (2013 e): On the Lathrobium fauna of Japan (Coleoptera: Staphylinidae: Paederinae). - Linzer biologische Beitrage 45 (2): 1615 - 1641." type="journal article" year="2013">ASSING 2013e</bibRefCitation>
). The currently known distribution, including the above record, is mapped in 
<bibRefCitation id="E41D7B9BE349805CFE37FCDD46BDFCEB" author="ASSING V" box="[501,665,829,851]" pageId="2" pageNumber="1645" pagination="1615 - 1641" refId="ref6442" refString="ASSING V. (2013 e): On the Lathrobium fauna of Japan (Coleoptera: Staphylinidae: Paederinae). - Linzer biologische Beitrage 45 (2): 1615 - 1641." type="journal article" year="2013">ASSING (2013e)</bibRefCitation>
. The above male is the first known macropterous male.
</paragraph>
